<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> Because Chayefsky started writing the screenplay during the same month that newscaster <a href="/wiki/Christine_Chubbuck" title="Christine Chubbuck">Christine Chubbuck</a> committed on-air suicide, some, including <a href="/w/index.php?title=Matthew_C._Ehrlich&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Matthew C. Ehrlich (page does not exist)">Matthew C. Ehrlich</a> in <i>Journalism in the Movies</i> (<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0252029348" class="internal">ISBN 0252029348</a>), have speculated (p. 122) that the scene was inspired by Chubbuck's manner of death.</li>
